chest /tʃɛst/

(chests) 

1. N-COUNT Your chest is the top part of the front of your body where your ribs, lungs, and heart are. 胸部 

例： He crossed his arms over his chest. 他在胸前交叉双臂。 

例： He was shot in the chest. 他胸部中弹。 

2. N-COUNT A chest is a large, heavy box used for storing things. 储物箱 

例： At the very bottom of the chest were his carving tools. 在储物箱的最底部有他的雕刻工具。 

例： ...a treasure chest. …一个珍宝箱。

